---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="PortixOne vs QZ Tray">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500"><a href="/compare" class="hover:text-slate-300">← Compare</a></p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold">PortixOne vs QZ Tray</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300">
      QZ Tray is a mature, widely-used local print bridge with a long track record — a solid choice
      today, especially if you need its broader driver support right now. Verify current details on
      <a href="https://qz.io" class="text-emerald-400 hover:underline">qz.io</a> before deciding;
      specifics below can go stale.
    </p>

    <table class="mt-8 w-full border-collapse text-sm">
      <thead>
        <tr class="border-b border-slate-800 text-left text-slate-400">
          <th class="py-2 pr-4">&nbsp;</th>
          <th class="py-2 pr-4">PortixOne</th>
          <th class="py-2">QZ Tray</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-800">
        <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400">Open source</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Yes</td><td class="py-3">Partial</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400">Silent printing</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Yes</td><td class="py-3">Yes</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400">Maturity</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Early (MVP)</td><td class="py-3">Mature, long track record</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400">Device scope today</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Windows, local printing</td><td class="py-3">Broad — printers, scanners, more</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="py-3 pr-4 text-slate-400">API model</td><td class="py-3 pr-4">Capability-based (print, cut, drawer, ...)</td><td class="py-3">Driver/device-specific</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="mt-8 text-slate-300">
      If you need something production-proven today across many device types, QZ Tray is a
      reasonable choice. PortixOne's bet is a simpler developer experience and a vendor-agnostic
      capability model — worth it once we've matched QZ Tray's maturity, not necessarily before.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
